#note probably the play that lost me the game. to me, the chance of an -ING bingo seemed most damaging. I can also maximize my chances of drawing the blank by turning over tiles. however, this does leave me vulnerable to pulling the Q and getting outrun if he bingos on row 14. if I play VARY at O1, I keep a U as Q insurance. a look at the bingo stats suggests that most racks that bingo at the top-left also bingo at the bottom-right. also, after VIRTUAL there are only 3 in the bag, so he's more likely to draw an out-play if he bingos. looks like a game-losing mistake in hindsight.
>Michael_Tang: ?DEEINW 14I WIDENEd +80 398
#note michael could pass up a bingo himself here and play AWE at 8H. tough call, but he went for the throat.
>JD: CEENQRW 13K ENEW +28 435
#note this or EWER best. Another reason why VARY looks stronger is that the game requires much more skill for Michael to win. after VARY, with his rack of DEEINW?, he can either bingo on column A to draw the score even and have to play an endgame with 6 tiles on his rack, or play WITHY at 9F for 31 (probably the correct play). After VIRTUAL he just needs to bingo and then find an out-play.
